    "abstractNote": "In the XVIIIth and XIXth centuries, the house of Deacon Am\u012br\u0161\u0101h Fat\u1e25\u012b of Diyarbak\u0131r stood at the epicenter of the events relating to the ancient-Syrian community of Syriac heritage in the Ottoman Empire, having a say in the election of patriarchs in Mardin and the union attempts between the Syrian Orthodox Church of Antioch and the Catholic Church. The Cogias Fat\u1e25\u012b derived their authority from the means generated by their trading house, which participated in the 1700\u2019s in international commerce between Persia, the Ottoman lands and Europe. Their story is narrated using around twenty archives East and West.",
